U.K. stocks rebound, sending the
FTSE 100 Index up 0.6 percent to 5,781.37 at 3:42 p.m. in
 London . The benchmark gauge briefly erased losses after data
showed U.S. house sales unexpectedly declined in March.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
